president bush pledged friday unswerving us 
support for captive nations peoples and countries that live under 
foreign domination or ideologies that are inimical to the ideas 
of national sovereignty and individual liberty 
bush proclaimed captive nations week calling for all nations of 
the world to guarantee human rights freedoms and independence for 
these peoples he said the meaning of this week is to live 
freedom to overcome oppression 
the president in a rose garden ceremony to mark the occasion 
cited rays of light worldwide that show changes in the soviet 
union and other countries toward openness and free expression 
including the dismantling of the barbed wire fence between austria 
and hungary 
to all nations america proclaims the truth cannot forever be 
intimidated by force for history shows and the human will 
proclaims that liberty can light the darkest night he said 
bush said the soviet unions baltic states of latvia lithuania 
and estonia are imbued with a spirit of renewal in their 
movements for independence 
he cited the opposition movements in china vietnam laos 
ethiopia and nicaragua and the ethnic turks in bulgaria saying 
america stands with the people involved in those struggles 
in his rose garden remarks bush pointed to his trip last week 
to hungary and poland two east bloc countries that are moving 
toward economic and politcal reform saying these are examples that 
freedom is in the air 
