at 12 he shot to fame when he was the only junior to hold 
kasparov to a draw during an exhibition of simultaneous chess games 
adams ranking might be threatened by other juniors joel 
lautier a french 15yearold has achieved two of the required 
three grandmaster performances 
and judit polgar 13 the youngest member of a remarkable trio 
of hungarian sisters missed her first grandmaster result at a 
tournament in new york in the spring by just half a point 
there are more opportunities now adams said there is so 
much more around for players at a younger age 
