the trouble started at 316 pm cdt 
the flight was about 1 hours out of denver some of the 
passengers were watching a sports videotape on the planes movie 
screens others were talking reading sleeping 
suddenly there was an explosion from the rear of the plane that 
knocked the flight attendants to the floor and then recalled 
david landsberger a businessman from caldwell nj we were 
going down 
jerome milford an indianapolis accountant returning from a 
colorado vacation said it was like going on an elevator and 
going down too fast we were losing altitude and they told us 
theyd lost an engine 
in the cockpit capt al c haynes who flew in the korean war 
and had been a united pilot for 33 years was telling air traffic 
controllers in minneapolis that the jet had lost an engine and was 
losing altitude one minute later he reported a complete 
hydraulic failure of the jets steering system the minneapolis 
tower told him to take the plane to dubuque iowa 
the federal aviation administration later discovered that a fan 
was missing from the tail engine it apparently had exploded 
slicing through the hydraulic steering system 
at 320 haynes declared an emergency and the flight was 
rerouted to sioux city iowa haynes told passengers that the plane 
had lost an engine and would be late 
