<TEXT>
italys new premier is one of western europes 
master politicians a man whose career embodies the nations 
political development since world war ii 
giulio andreotti 70 who helped draft italys postwar 
constitution formed his sixth government and italys 49th postwar 
government on saturday 
the christian democrat became part of the government in 1947 and 
has been a constant member since heading the ministries of 
defense treasury finance interior industry budget and most 
recently the foreign ministry 
the original teflon politician andreotti has survived numerous 
controversies and formal inquests power wears down whoever 
doesnt have it is one of his bestknown phrases 
he is known for his brilliance his dry wit and his remarkable 
grasp of issues a stooped man with protruding ears andreotti also 
a favorite target of italian political cartoonists 
andreotti a roman catholic with close ties to the vatican was 
born to a roman schoolteacher and his wife and earned a degree in 
law at rome university 
during world war ii he became a protege of alcide de gasperi 
who helped found the christian democrat party and became italys 
foremost postwar statesman 
at the age of 28 andreotti became undersecretary of state 
beginning a long career that earned him the nickname minister for 
life he was elected to parliament in 1946 and has been 
continuously reelected to his seat 
andreotti has been premier during some of italys most difficult 
postwar days when right and leftwing terrorism plagued the 
nation and the economy slid on the day andreotti formed his fourth 
government in 1978 christian democrat leader aldo moro was 
kidnapped by the leftwing red brigades fiftyfour days later the 
politicians body was found in a trunk 
while andreotti maintained the countrys proamerican stance and 
firm ties to nato he became the first christian democrat premier 
to accept support from the communists to keep his government 
afloat the communists nearly overtook the christian democrats in 
the late 1970s but have since lost much support 
andreottis career has been marked by controversy in september 
1984 he caused an international furor by speaking out against a 
possible reunification of east germany and west germany 
domestically he has been cleared in numerous parliamentary 
inquiries into charges against him ranging from corruption to 
obstructing probes of a 1969 bomb attack thought to be the work of 
rightwing terrorists 
the author of several topselling books on religious and 
political issues andreotti also is an avid fan of the roma 
professional soccer team his interests range from latin to stamp 
collecting 
andreotti is married to livia danese they have four children 
</TEXT>
