a recent verdict reviving the historic brown 
vs topeka board of education case was withdrawn without 
explanation by a federal appeals court in denver baffling both 
sides in the case 
attorneys for both sides said they found out about the decision 
friday and said they were unsure what the unusual action by the 
court means for the topeka school system 
were in the same position now as if no opinion had ever been 
filed said robert hoecker clerk of the 10th us circuit court 
of appeals in denver 
in 1987 us district court judge richard rogers of topeka 
ruled that topekas public school district had no illegal 
intentional systematic or residual separation of races 
in june the appeals court overturned rogers ruling it said 
the topeka school system had not done enough to overcome remnants 
