john m cranor iii a top executive at 
pepsico inc was appointed friday as president and chief executive 
of the food and soft drink makers kentucky fried chicken corp 
subsidiary 
cranor 42 formerly president of pepsicola east will succeed 
richard p mayer who resigned to become president of general foods 
usa said d wayne calloway chairman of the board and chief 
executive of pepsico based in purchase ny 
were very fortunate to have a leader of john cranors caliber 
to succeed dick calloway said in a news release we have great 
confidence in the entire kfc organization and look forward to even 
greater success in the years ahead under johns leadership 
kfc is the worlds secondlargest quick service restaurant 
system with about 8000 restaurants generating sales of nearly 6 
billion it was acquired by pepsico in october 1986 
cranor has held a series of marketing operations and general 
management positions in the restaurant soft drinks and snack food 
businesses 
he began his pepsico career in 1977 as marketing group manager 
at fritolay where he eventually served as vice president of new 
business development and vice president of marketing 
cranor then was a senior vice president and later president of 
wilson sporting goods then a pepsico subsidiary 
in 1985 he joined taco bell and became division vice president 
making him responsible for 1300 restaurants in the united states 
he then became president of pepsicos fountain beverage operations 
in 1986 
cranor was promoted to president of pepsicola east in february 
1988 making him responsible for all pepsi operations in the 
northeast 
