<TEXT>
the proposed reorganization plan filed friday by 
eastern airlines specifies four options for consumers holding 
eastern tickets issued before the companys march 9 bankruptcy 
filing 
applying for a cash refund with interest 
using the ticket for travel of equal value with a free upgrade 
to first class when space is available 
using the ticket for travel of equal value with the right to 
buy a companion ticket for half the normal fare 
exchanging the ticket for travel credits valued at 135 percent 
of the ticket being exchanged 
